This is a nifty app for all sorts of unit conversion. Included are length, area, weight, volume, currency (which gets updated for up-to-date rates), temp, time, speed, pressure, force, work, power, angle, data, fuel and cooking (!). Many aspects are configurable, for instance the country of residence for the starting units (eg. meters if you live in France but feet if you live in the USA), what currency to convert to etc. The ads in the free version aren't intrusive nor obnoxious (although they use up a good quarter of the screen area), but come on, the full program is only 1.99 US $, and a lot of love and care went into making this app. Pros: - Great GUI, simple to understand and use - Tons of units available - Easy to customize Cons: - Colors in GUI kinda limited. It's a matter of taste I know, but the schemes available didn't do it for me. - I would have loved even more precision on the data converter (eg. converting terabytes to bits). - I didn't know it existed sooner!
